                            ;************************************************************************************************
                            ;*                                           FUNCTION                                           *
                            ;************************************************************************************************
                            ;undefined LoadSegmentFromDisk()
                            ;Loads a segment from disk at the top of memory.
                            ;If there is sufficient memory for the segment, it subtracts
                            ;the length of the segment from the top of prog stack (KP) 
                            ;and loads the segment there.
                            ;
                            ;on entry:
                            ;  A=Segment#
                            ;  KP=current top of prog stack
                            ;
                            ;on success:
                            ;  KP is reduced by seg length
                            ;  requested seg loaded at previous KP
                            ;
                            ;on error:
                            ;  most likely has thrown appropriate error, 
                            ;  eg stack overflow, IO error
